and cultural contributions. This volume of new essays applies current discourse on generations in German culture to contemporary works dealing with major sociohistorical events since the Nazi period. Contributors: Svea Bräunert, Laurel Cohen-Pfister, Friederike Eigler, Thomas C. Fox, Katharina Gerstenberger, Erin McGlothlin, Brad Prager, Ilka Rasch, Susanne Rinner, Caroline Schaumann, Maria Stehle, Reinhild Steingröver, Susanne Vees-Gulani. Laurel Cohen-Pfister is Associate Professor of German at Gettysburg College, and Susanne Vees-Gulani is Assistant Professor of German and Comparative Literature at Case Western Reserve University.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aCollective memoryzGermany. 0aGerman literaturexHistory and criticismy20th century. 0aGerman literaturexHistory and criticismy21st century. 0aIntergenerational relationszGermany. 0aLiterature and historyzGermany. 0aMass media and culturezGermany. 0aNational characteristics, German, in literature. 4aGerman Literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aFirst World War.  aGenerational Shifts.  aGerman culture.  aGerman identity.  aNazi era.  aNazi period.  aPostwar division.  aSocialhistorical events.  aTwentieth-century German history.1 aBräunert, Svea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCohen-Pfister, Laurel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCohen-Pfister, Laurel, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aEigler, Friederike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFox, Thomas C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGerstenberger, Katharina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcGlothlin, Erin, econtributor.4ctb4https://